

To install AOLserver:


1.      Download, configure, build and install Tcl 8.4 with threads
	enabled.  AOLserver requires Tcl at runtime and for
	configuration and bulid.  The following should work:

	cd /my/build/dir
	cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.tcl.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/tcl \
	 co -r core-8-4-0 -d tcl8.4 tcl
	cd tcl8.4/unix
	./configure --enable-threads --prefix=/usr/local/aolserver
	make install


2.      If you don't have GNU make (Linux make is GNU make), install
	it as AOLserver's module makefiles to include the results
	of configuration.  Get it at http://www.gnu.org.


3.      Download, configure, build, and install AOLserver.  The
	following should work:

	cd /my/build/dir
	cvs -d \
	 :pserver:anonymous@cvs.aolserver.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/aolserver \
	 co aolserver
	cd aolserver	
	./configure --with-tcl=/usr/local/aolserver/lib
	gmake install


4.      Create an nsd.tcl startup script.  The following should get
	you started:

	cd /usr/local/aolserver
	cp sample-config.tcl nsd.tcl
	vi nsd.tcl


5.	Try it out:

	cd /usr/local/aolserver
	bin/nsd -ft nsd.tcl



For more information, check http://www.aolserver.com.

jgdavidson
